@NODE "Einf" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{i}Apper@{ui} is an AppIcon, that can be fully controlled by the user.
By dropping an icon Apper will execute any shell command, so that you can
create many useful tools for your workbench.

Please try the examples.

@{"Back" LINK "Main"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Konf" "Configuration"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}Apper can only be started from Workbench and not from shell!!!!@{ub}

You can setup Apper via Tooltypes:

@{b}COMMAND=@{ub}     enter here the shell command, that will be executed 
                      when an icon is dropped. The string "%s" will be
                      replaced by the filename.
                      (e.g. COMMAND=more %s)

@{b}WINDOW=@{ub}      here you can define your output window (console).
                      Preset: CON:0/10/640/100/Ausgabe/AUTO/CLOSE/WAIT

@{b}ICONX=@{ub}      x-position of your Appicon!

@{b}ICONY=@{ub}      y-position of your Appicon!

Apper will take the program icon for your AppIcon. So you can copy Apper,
rename it and change its icon to create several utilities.

@{"Back" LINK "MAIN"}

@ENDNODE

